  scenario="It is midnight on a Thursday. A letting agent managing forty rental properties across east Oxford types: 'Hi — I manage forty rental properties and need a reliable Gas Safe engineer for our annual CP12 programme. Current engineer has retired. Properties are a mix of combi boilers (mostly Worcester, Vaillant, and Ideal), some older system boilers with cylinders, and two properties still on old Baxi back boilers. About thirty-five need CP12 renewal between February and April. Also need a price for the two back boiler conversions to modern combis — tenants are complaining about the noise and the pilot light going out. Can you handle a programme this size and maintain our three-year service history records? We need certificates uploaded to our property management portal within 48 hours of each visit.' Without chat, she emails Friday. With AI Website Chat, the AI confirms your Gas Safe registration and CP12 capability, asks about the geographic spread of properties and average radiator counts, and captures: 40 rentals east Oxford, 35 CP12s Feb-April, mix of Worcester/Vaillant/Ideal combis + system boilers + 2 Baxi back boilers, 2 back boiler conversions, service history, 48hr certificate upload to portal."
